OL,3,CState schools falling behind private
OL,4,Cschools in AI 'digital divide' ` report
OL,6,FJulie McCulloch, director of strategy
OL,7,Fand policy at the Association of
OL,8,FSchool and College Leaders, said: "We
OL,9,Fcannot afford to have AI technology in
OL,10,Feducation descend into yet another
OL,11,Fexample of haves and have-nots.
OL,13,F"The fact is that the technology,
OL,14,Ftraining and resources needed to
OL,15,Futilise AI are expensive and require
OL,16,Ftime and sufficient staffing.
OL,18,F"This puts schools at a disadvantage
OL,19,Fwhere these things are in short supply.
